All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AbsNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to compute the absolute value of a value (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    AddNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to add two objects (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    AndNode
    The node model used to perform logical AND.
    ClampNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to clamp a value in a specific range (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    ColorDialogBox
    A modal dialog box that pops to ask the user to input a color using a color wheel.
    ColorFieldPanel
    A property field for Color.
    CompareNode<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The node model used to compare two objects.
    ControlPanel
    Part of the game window responsible for interacting with the game.
    It hosts the nodal widget and the element managers.
    The elements managers are ElementDetailPanel instances.
    They are derivated from JToolBar which allows the user to freely rearrange their positions.
    ConvertDoubleIntApproxNode
    The node model used to replace a double with the closest integer.
    ConvertDoubleIntNode
    The node model used to split a double into an integer part (simply the truncated value) and the residue (the fractional part).
    ConvertIntDoubleNode
    The node model used to cast an integer as a double.
    CurEntityNode
    The node model used to get the entity being processed.
    CurSpeciesNode
    The node model used to get the species being processed.
    DeathRule
    Rule used to kill entities.
    DimNode
    The node model used to get the game's grid dimensions.
    DivDoubleNode
    The node model used to divide a double with another one.
    DivEuclNode
    The node model used to compute the euclidean division of an integer (dividend) by another integer (divisor).
    DivIntNode
    The node model used to double value corresponding to the division of an integer with another one.
    DivVectorNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to divide a vector with a value (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    Edge
    This class provides the abstract edge model for the edges used in the nodal system.
    Element
    A simple class that hold a name and image attributes, useful for reusing interface elements on species and surfaces
    ElementDetailPanel
    This class is used to display the details of an element.
    In practice it's used as a part of the ElementManagerToolBar.
    It's mainly composed of property fields panel.

    Don't directly use this class, but instead use the surface or species derivated ones as they have additionnal fields specific to those element subclasses.
    ElementManagerToolBar<T extends Element>
    Create an element manager as a tool bar.

    Includes the list for the different elements,
    buttons to add/remove/rearrange them,
    a viewer to inspect and modify a specific element.
    Entity
    Each entity is part of a species.
    EntityInAreaNode
    The node model used to detect if an entity is in a rectangular area.
    EntityNode
    The node model used to extract data from an entity.
    EqualNode<T>
    The node model used to test equality between two objects.
    GameFrame
    The game's window.
    It's basically composed of a MenuBar on top, a ControlPanel on the left side and a WorldPanel on the right side.
    GameManager
    The game manager is responsible for the initialization and evolution of the game state at each frame using the rules defined by the user.
    GameManagerBuilder
    Class with only static methods meant to build new game managers when the user wants to start a new project or to load previously saved projects.
    GamePlayer
    Object in charge of playing and pausing the game simulation.
    GenerateNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a generation rule's network.
    GenerationRule
    Rule used to generate new members in a species.
    IfElseNode<T>
    The node model used to perform an IF/ELSE statement.
    ImageFile
    Utility class used for handling images in the saving and loading process.
    Input
    This class provides the abstract model for the input(s) of the nodes in the nodal system.
    KillNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a death rule's network.
    LoadEvent
    A simple ActionEvent that carries a gameManager reference, used to trigger ActionListeners after loading a savefile.
    Main
    Class starting the game by opening a NewWorldDialogBox to create a GameManager, and a GameFrame and a GamePlayer linked to it respectively to display and update over time the GameManager.
    It's possible to skip the NewWorldDialogBox by launching the app with at least 2 arguments being a width and a height.
    MaxNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to compute the max of two objects (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    MinNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to compute the min of two objects (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    MovementRule
    Rule used to move entities.
    MoveNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a movement rule's network.
    MultiplyIntDoubleNode
    This node allows to multiply int with double.
    MultiplyNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to multiply two objects (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    MultiplyVectorNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to multiply a vector with a value (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    Network
    This class provides the abstract model for the networks with in the nodal system when defining rules for the game.
    NetworkIOException
    Exception raised by an input or an output when it is asked to read or write an invalid data (usually a null value).
    NewWorldDialogBox
    The dialog box that will pop to start a new world.
    This dialog box proposes 8 options to create a new world.
    Some of those options requires to give terrain dimensions, which can be done using the text fields at the bottom.
    NewWorldTemplate
    This class holds all the information needed by the GameManagerBuilder class to create the wanted GameManager.
    NewWorldTemplatePanel
    A panel displaying a NewWorldTemplate composed on the top of the template's name, at the bottom of the 2 description lines of the template, and on the center of a button with the template's image.
    The panel can be selected or not, and its button color change depending on that value.
    NodalEditor
    The controller class for nodal editors.
    NodalEditorBuilder
    A class with only static methods, meant to build the standard node editors we use in the software.
    Node
    This class provides the abstract node model for the nodes used in the nodal system.
    NotNode
    The node model used to negate a boolean.
    OneMinusNode
    The node model used to compute 1-x for any double x.
    OppositeValueNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to compute the opposite of a value (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    OrNode
    The node model used to perform a logical OR.
    Output
    This class provides the abstract model for the output(s) of the nodes in the nodal system.
    OutsideNode
    The node model used to know if a given position is inside the terrain or not.
    PowNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to perform a power calculation.
    PrinterMessage
    Simple class to hold a message to print.
    PrinterToolBar
    ToolBar holding the printer and its related component, including 2 JToggbleButtons and one TextFieldPanel.
    The JToggleButtons
    PrintNode<T>
    The node model used to print informations on an object, using its toString method.
    PropertyFieldPanel
    The property field class is a panel where a property is represented by a JLabel that displays the property name and a component that depends on the property.
    This class should be derived depending on the property type you want.
    For each derived class, remeber to add a field/button to display and interact with your property value, as this class only displays its name.
    RandBoolNode
    The node model used to generate a random boolean following a Bernoulli law.
    RandDoubleNode
    The node model used to generate a random number in the range [0, 1[.
    RandGaussDoubleNode
    The node model used to generate a random double following a normal law.
    RandIntNode
    The node model used to generate a random integer in the range [0, bound[.
    Rule<T extends TerminalNode>
    Abstract model for the rules defined by the user through a network of operators.
    Saver
    The goal of the Saver class is to save and load a project's GameManager from a savefile.

    Saving a project is done in several steps.
    The first one is to create a temporary work folder.
    Then we serialize the GameManger into a txt file in this folder.
    After, another txt file is created to list all the images used by the surfaces.
    Species
    A species represents a group of homogeneous entities, which all behave according to the same rules.
    SpeciesDetailPanel
    Derived class to display all the properties of a species.
    SpeciesInAreaNode
    The node model used to detect if a species has at least one member in a rectangular area, and if so record its position.
    SpeciesNode
    The node model used to extract data from a species.
    SubNode<T>
    The abstract node model used to substract two objects (concrete subclasses are instanciated by static methods).
    Surface
    Each instance of this class represents a different kind of surface that can be stored on a tile.
    SurfaceAtNode
    The node model used to get the surface in the tile at a given position.
    SurfaceDetailPanel
    Derived class to display all the properties of a surface.
    TerminalNode<R extends Rule>
    Abstract class for terminal nodes which are connected to rules.
    Terrain
    Representation of the terrain as a list of slots.
    TerrainManagerToolBar
    ToolBar for viewing and editing the terrain.
    It includes a visualizer of the different models and buttons to re-arrange them, delete one or add one.
    It also displays the dimensions of the terrain as well as the terrain trigger time (that last one can be modified)
    TerrainModel
    Abstract representation of a terrain model.
    TerrainModelEllipse
    A terrain model that represents an elliptic area.
    TerrainModelErode
    Decreases the area of the terrain given in argument: a position will be included in the new terrain if it and all of its direct neighbors is included in the original terrain.
    Each position has 4 neighbors : up, down, left and right.
    TerrainModelExpand
    Increases the area of the terrain given in argument: a position will be included in the new terrain if it or any of its direct neighbors is included in the original terrain.
    Each position has 4 neighbors : up, down, left and right.
    TerrainModelFill
    The point of this model is to easily have a completely filled TerrainSlot
    TerrainModelIntersection
    Result in the intersection of 2 TerrainModels.
    TerrainModelInvert
    Invert the surface occupied by a TerrainModel.
    TerrainModelMask
    A terrain model used to mask a terrain model with another one (substraction).
    TerrainModelRandom
    A terrain model with randomly placed terrain units following a given density.
    TerrainModelRectangle
    A terrain model that represents a rectangular area.
    TerrainModelUnion
    Result in the Union of 2 TerrainModels.
    TerrainNode<T extends TerrainModel>
    Abstract model for nodes used in the terrain network to define a specific terrain layer.
    TerrainNodeEllipse
    The node model used to create an elliptic terrain layer.
    TerrainNodeErode
    The node model used to erode another model.
    TerrainNodeExpand
    The node model used to expand another model.
    TerrainNodeFill
    The node model used to have a completely filled up layer.
    TerrainNodeIntersect
    The node model used to intersect two terrain layers.
    TerrainNodeInvert
    The node model used to invert another model.
    TerrainNodeMask
    The node model used to mask a terrain layer with another one.
    TerrainNodeRandom
    The node model used to create a randomized terrain layer.
    TerrainNodeRectangle
    The node model used to create a rectangular terrain layer.
    TerrainNodeUnion
    The node model used to join two terrain layers.
    TerrainNodeUnit
    The node model used to create a terrain layer that covers only one tile.
    TerrainSlot
    Representation of a slot used to link the terrain network to the actual terrain model.
    TerrainVisualizerPanel
    Complete visualizer of the terrainSlots of a Terrain.
    It display the visualization of the slots (using a TerrainStackVisualizer) as well as buttons to change the focused slot, and buttons to add/move/remove the slots.
    TextFieldPanel
    A property field for text that can be edited.
    TextFixedFieldPanel
    A property field for a NON editable text.
    TimeNode
    The node model used to get the current frame.
    TrigoAngleVectorsNode
    The node model used to compute the angle between two vectors.
    TrigoConvertDegRadNode
    The node model used to convert degrees to radians.
    TrigoConvertRadDegNode
    The node model used to convert radians to degrees.
    TrigoCosNode
    The node model used to calculate the cosine of an angle.
    TrigoPINode
    The node model used to provide the constant value PI.
    TrigoRadialToVector
    The node model used to create a vector by specifying its angle and norm.
    TrigoSinNode
    The node model used to calculate the sine of an angle.
    VariableNode<T>
    The node model used to represent a single variable, parametrized by the variable's type.
    Vec2D
    An instance of the Vec2D class is a 2D vector with integer coordinates.
    Some basic operations for these vectors are implemented, such as addition, substraction, equality testing, dot product, etc.
    VectGatherNode
    The node model used to gather two integers to form a 2D vector.
    VectNormNode
    The node model used to calculate the norm of a vector.
    VectScalarProductNode
    The node model used to calculate the scalar product of two vectors.
    VectSplitNode
    The node model used to split a 2D vector into two integers (its components).
    VectVectorialProductNode
    The node model used to calculate the vectorial product of two vectors.
    WorldPanel
    This class manages how the display of the world.
    The display consists of grid of tile representing the map.
    XorNode
    The node model used to calculate the eXclusive-OR (XOR) on two booleans.
